          <td>
            <table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="2">
              <tr> 
                <td class="chblue"><font class="h1font"> Beginner Decks</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="3"><tr><td><font class="bfont"><table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0"><tr><td colspan="2"><font class="h1font">Lightning Striking Again</font></td></tr><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Rating</Font></TD><TD><img src="/magination/gfx/star3.gif" width="21" height="22" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/magination/gfx/star3.gif" width="21" height="22" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/magination/gfx/star3.gif" width="21" height="22" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/magination/gfx/star3.gif" width="21" height="22" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size=1>(4.00)</font> | <A HREF="/magination/decks/decks.php?reviews=23900">Read Reviews</A></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Author</font></TD><TD><font class="bfont"> <A HREF="http://www.decktech.net/magination/main/mpage.php?member=9064">Danny "Woven" Young</A></FONT> <font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/magination/main/mpage.php?member=9064&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a></font></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Description</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> Trying to teach beginners to play, I found that they frequently complain about the duel going too slowly. This beginner&#39;s Arderial deck attempts to remedy the problem.</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Submitted</Font></TD><TD><font class="bfont"> June 12, 2002</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Cards</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> Magi:<br>
<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(526)">Aula</a>-Cloud Scepter, <a href="javascript:card_browser(519)">Brannix</a><br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(342)">Lasada</a>-<a href="javascript:card_browser(337)">Xyx</a>, <a href="javascript:card_browser(335)">Thunder Vashp</a>,<a href="javascript:card_browser(356)">Shooting Star</a><br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(665)">Elios</a><br>
<br>
Creatures: <br>
<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(325)">Ayebaw</a>- 2<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(664)">Shock Vashp</a>- 2<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(335)">Thunder Vashp</a>- 3<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(519)">Brannix</a>- 2<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(337)">Xyx</a>- 3<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(339}<a href="javascript:card_browser({337)">Xyx</a> Minor</a>- 3<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(525)">Yarothis</a>- 1<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(523)">Vemment</a>- 2<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(329}<a href="javascript:card_browser({354)">Lightning</a> Hyren</a>- 2<br>
<br>
Spells:<br>
<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(669)">Cataclysm</a>- 1<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(355)">Shockwave</a>- 2<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(670}<a href="javascript:card_browser({528)">Sorreah</a>&#39;s Dream</a>- 2<br>
Shotting Star- 3<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(354)">Lightning</a>- 3<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(358)">Updraft</a>- 2<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(353)">Fog Bank</a>- 2<br>
Crushing Winds- 1<br>
<br>
Relics:<br>
<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(785}<a href="javascript:card_browser({557)">Maelstrom</a> Flask</a>- 2<br>
Cloud Scepter- 2<br>
Arderian Guard Wings- 2<br>
<br>
Total: 42 and 3 magi   </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> Got a beginner&#39;s need for speed? This may be the answer you are looking for. I give you this warning though- beginners may have trouble getting the cards for this, as it has cards from all released sets. Therefore, you, as the teacher, should help them build it. The resource drain is not much- the only rares are the Ayebaws.<br>
<br>
As I&#39;ve said before, the beginners I tried to teach wanted the duel to go faster, so I came home and built this. This deck is all about aggresion.<br>
<br>
Your first magi is Aula. If your oponent is Arderial, the Brannix gives you a nice starting edge. Aula is here to get what you want off the bat. If at all possible, go second so you can see what your enemy has on the field. Got a swarm? Windsight and Scepter for the Cataclysm, then drop a Xyx or two. Got a big creature problem? Look for a Shockwave. Bograth super swarm? Grab a Lightning Hyren or two. Burrow? Get out those Shock Vashp(note to teachers- you may want to add Rayje&#39;s Swords if Burrow is prevalent in your area, or relic removal if you see a bunch of relics. Beam of Light may be nice.). Is Cald burning you? Guard Wings. Core got you down? Fetch that Yarothis. If you must go first, Ayebaw give you a nice edge- drop the Ayebaw, pump it/them up next turn, then blow through the enemy forces. But remember not to insanely draw just because you can- if you have a good hand, keep it.   <br>
<br>
Lasada is a very nice beginning magi. He is armed with a 6 energize, and his hand lets you defeat a small creature and hit a magi. If he falls, your next magi gets 3 more cards. Quite versatile.<br>
<br>
Elios. Ok, I know he may confuse some new people, but seriously, what other uncommon Arderial magi can do the job better? (Not Shimmer Andrew, Storm Shields don&#39;t belong here ;) )<br>
When Elios the board, take a look at your surroundings. Do you have a nice hand? Choose a small number and let it fly. Do you have no hand what-so-ever? Choose a large number that still gives you some protection. A little while ago, I wrote an article on Elios, so you may want to check that out. He can warp his energy to suit his needs; if you have junk in your hand, but have a Cloud Scepter, you can skip your draw step, or at least reduce it to one card, to super-pump Elios. Your draw step is replaced by the Scepter, which, by the way, has arguably the coolest quote in all Magi-Nation.<br>
<br>
Enjoy :)<br>
<br>
Danny Young<br>
<br>
